{
  "stem": "4753.9",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But somehow, I always escaped when I saw the smoke, what I did see all the time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But when that really hit me, and all the things depressed me or something-- I don't even know if that was the right expression-- then I close my eyes, and I was back in my thought in my home with my parents, and my sister, and brothers.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I heard them talk to each other and to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I came from a city where there were agriculture city-- you know, were fruit-growers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the whole city in springtime was full of cherry blossom, and apple blossom, and so on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So the whole city was like a perfumed atmosphere.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I even smelled that in concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I escaped to that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Unfortunately, right now, and after the war, [SIGHS] I am still in two places at once.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I am here in Los Angeles, thank God.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I am very happy to be in America.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I am in Auschwitz also, every single day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I just can't escape that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I talked about the 10 girls who were together from the very beginning, making a pact that we are camp sisters and standing together five in a row every morning, two rows together in roll calls.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We really did stay together.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whenever there was a selection, we tried to help each other.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If someone was very weak, we put the person in the middle of the five as we were standing in line, so the SS shouldn't notice them, so-- well, we pinched each other's face, so we should looked healthier.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we always, always encouraged each other.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We always told each other we would be free.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Naturally, there was always one of us who was down and cried, didn't want to live anymore.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
